
The libvirt library is an open source API and management tool for managing platform virtualization.It can be used to manage Linux KVM, Xen, VMware qemu and other virtualization technologies.
 
step 1: Run XEN setup
step 2: Install libvirt-dev package using the command
	 sudo apt-get install libvirt-dev
step3: open terminal and compile the program using 
		gcc libvirt.c -lvirt 
step4:open virtual machine manager using the command 
	 sudo virt-manager 
then run the program and see the changes.
